        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2019-07-11 12:22:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 12:\n\nCan this please be merged?  This is to fix SDNC clustering - SDNC currently breaks if brought up in a cluster due to all cluster members trying to create and initialize the database.  This fixes that by moving database initialization out of the startup script (run on each container) and into a post install job (run only once per deployment).  I verified this fix in my CCSDK windriver environment.",
        "patchset_number": 12
      },
